From: Nick <nick@local>
Subject: [PATCH] media: rkcif: don't drop frames or reset CTRL on CSI size errors

When a MIPI CSI-2 source sends multiple Virtual Channels but only some
CIF IDs are actively capturing, the unused VCs trigger CSI_SIZE_ERR
interrupts. The current IRQ handler does two things that kill multi-VC
throughput:

1. It bounces the MIPI LVDS CTRL register (0x000A0000) on every size
   error, which resets the receiver and forces re-sync, losing frames.

2. It returns early after the reset, dropping frame-end events for
   active capture IDs that arrived in the same interrupt.

This severely impacts multi-VC sensors like the NVP6324 where 4 channels
are multiplexed over one MIPI link. With only one channel captured, the
other 3 VCs continuously trigger size errors, reducing the active
channel's capture rate from 25fps to ~5fps.

Fix: skip the CTRL reset (which was the main throughput killer) and
clear the CSI_SIZE_ERR bits from the local intstat instead of returning.
This allows frame-end events for active IDs to be properly handled even
when size errors occur simultaneously from unused IDs.

---
 drivers/media/platform/rockchip/cif/capture.c | 15 +++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/rockchip/cif/capture.c b/drivers/media/platform/rockchip/cif/capture.c
--- a/drivers/media/platform/rockchip/cif/capture.c
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/rockchip/cif/capture.c
@@ -14229,10 +14229,17 @@
 				cif_dev->csi_host_idx = tmp_csi_host_idx;
 			} else {
-				rkcif_write_register_or(cif_dev, CIF_REG_MIPI_LVDS_CTRL, 0x000A0000);
-				if (cif_dev->chip_id >= CHIP_RV1103B_CIF)
-					rkcif_write_register_and(cif_dev, CIF_REG_MIPI_LVDS_CTRL, ~0x000f0000);
+				/*
+				 * Skip the CTRL reset (0x000A0000) for multi-VC.
+				 * Bouncing the MIPI receiver on size errors from
+				 * unused virtual channels forces re-sync and kills
+				 * throughput on active capture IDs.
+				 */
 			}
-			return;
+			/*
+			 * Don't return - clear size error bits and continue
+			 * processing frame-end events for active capture IDs.
+			 */
+			intstat &= ~CSI_SIZE_ERR;
 		}
 
 		if (intstat & CSI_FIFO_OVERFLOW_V1) {
